<div class="block-contributor">
		

		<div class="block-contributor-content">
		<div class="block-contributor-bio small">
			<p><span class="smallcaps"><strong>Jamie Berger</strong></span> moved from New York City to San Francisco in 1992 after finishing a master&rsquo;s degree in poetry. He hasn&rsquo;t written a poem since. His two monologues, <em>Knowing the Questions</em> and <em>Regrets Only</em>, had extended runs in San Francisco and New York. His writing has appeared in the<em> San Francisco Chronicle</em>, McSweeneys.net, and <em>Negative Capability</em>.</p><a href="/contributors/jamie-berger" class="block-contributor-link link-alt small">More From This Contributor&nbsp;&#9656;</a>		</div>
	</div>
</div>

